    "result": {"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"videoId":null,"videoLocaleIds":null,"bilibiliIds":null,"title":"Task 24","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Now that you know how to use <code>do</code> to form questions about hobbies, let's use <code>do</code> to ask about daily routines. This is useful for finding out about someone's everyday activities, which is a common topic of small talk.</p>\n<p>Note: When you use <code>do</code> as an auxiliary verb in a question, the main verb must stay in its base form. For example:</p>\n<p>Statement: <code>She works as a Full Stack dev.</code></p>\n<p>Question: <code>Does she work as a Full Stack dev?</code></p>\n<p><code>work</code> stays as <code>work</code> and does not change to <code>works</code>, even when asking about a third person singular subject like <code>he,</code> <code>she,</code> or <code>it.</code></p>\n</section>","challengeType":19,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-conversation-starters-in-the-break-room","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-conversation-starters-in-the-break-room/task-24","blockName":"learn-conversation-starters-in-the-break-room","tests":[]},"question":{"text":"<p>Choose the question that correctly uses <code>do</code> to ask about daily activities.</p>","answers":[{"answer":"<p><code>Do you write code every day?</code></p>","feedback":null},{"answer":"<p><code>Do you writes code every day?</code></p>","feedback":"<p>Remember, after <code>do,</code> the main verb should not end in <code>s.</code></p>"},{"answer":"<p><code>Writes you code every day?</code></p>","feedback":"<p>The word order is incorrect in this option; <code>do</code> should be at the beginning</p>"},{"answer":"<p><code>You do write code every day?</code></p>","feedback":"<p>This option uses <code>do</code> in a statement, not a question.</p>"}],"solution":1},"scene":null,"translationPending":false,"assignments":[],"audioPath":null}}},"